The paper deals with distributed algorithms for graph optimization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of distributed computing (cs.DC), graph theory (cs.DM), and theoretical computer science (cs.CC, cs.GT). The focus on parameterized problems suggests that cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) may also be a relevant sub-category.
